node.description: Event Number Reset through TTC when in local L1A mode
Orbit Number Reset through TTC when in local L1A mode
Save received DAQ data to monitor buffer
if '1', monitor buffer full will stop event builder
if '1', send all data to downstream when ttc reset is received
if '1', TTS outputs correspond to bits 0-3 of 0x19 instead of TTS state
For testing the DAQ Link SFP Connections
TTS output is TTC signal output
generate fake data upon recieving L1A
if '0', mem test uses 64bit PRBS. if '1', uses 32bit seq nums
Enabled error conditions of recorded events
Read back what was written to
Num of Evs Captured after Trigger
if '1', save every n EVN where n is determined by bits 19-22
PreScale Factor. 0xf low 5 bits 0, 0x0 low 50 bits 0
if '1', catches evs when CRC error
if '1', catches evs when evn/orn/bcnt mismatch
'0' indicates sync lost at corresponding AMC Port
'1' ttc_bcnt_reset only works once after system reset
Settable Part of Calibration WIN upper lim (bits 27-22 fixed 110110), default 100110
Settable Part of Calibration WIN lower lim (bits 11-6 fixed 110110), default 011101
'1' increments pg num by 128, '0' by 1 (only if run bit is '1')
Monitored Ev Size in 32-bit word. Returns '0' in run mode if no data available
Number of unread events captured by monitor
HTR CRC check error count of built events

DDR3 event data write port ready

Event data ready in event buffer of event builders

Write N to generate L1A every Nth orbit if bit 2 of 0x1 is set
'00' L1A per orbit, '10' per bunch crossing, '11' random
'00' all four rules, '01' not rule 4, '10' rule 1 & 2, '11' rule 1
V6 die temperature in unit of 0.1 degree Celsius
